extends layout
block content
  div(id='topbar', class='navbar navbar-default')
    p
      a(href='/', id='title') [ API Project ]
      span(id='author') By Agust√≠n Balmer

  div(id='main')
    p(class='whiteback')
      | API that uses the following technologies: 
      b Node.js
      |, 
      b Express.js
      |, 
      b MongoDB
      |, 
      b Pug.js
      |, 
      b Heroku 
      | and 
      b mLab
      br
      | to solve the backend challenges from 
      a(href='https://www.freecodecamp.com/challenges/timestamp-microservice') Freecodecamp
      | . Saved in 
      a(href='https://github.com/Balmer1/challenges-api') GitHub
      | .
    p(class='greyback')
      a(href="/timestamp",class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right")
      a(href="/timestamp")
        b   Timestamp Microservice  
      br
      | I can pass a string as a parameter, and it will check to see whether that string contains either a unix timestamp or a natural language date. If it does, it returns both the Unix timestamp and the natural language form of that date. If it does not contain a date or Unix timestamp, it returns null for those properties.
      br
    p(class='whiteback')
      a(href="/who",class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right")
      a(href="/who")
        b   Request Header Parser Microservice
      br
      | I can get the IP address, language and operating system for my browser.
    p(class='greyback')
      a(href="/shorturl",class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right")
      a(href="/shorturl")
        b   URL Shortener Microservice
      br
      | I can pass a URL as a parameter and I will receive a shortened URL in the JSON response. If I pass an invalid URL that doesn't follow the valid http://www.example.com format, the JSON response will contain an error instead. When I visit that shortened URL, it will redirect me to my original link.
    p(class='whiteback')
      a(href="/imagesearch",class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right")
      a(href="/imagesearch")
        b   Image Search Abstraction Layer
      br
      | I can get the image URLs, alt text and page urls for a set of images relating to a given search string. I can paginate through the responses by adding a ?offset=2 parameter to the URL. I can get a list of the most recently submitted search strings.
    p(class='greyback')
      a(href="/upload",class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right")
      a(href="/upload")
        b   File Metadata Microservice
      br
      | I can submit a FormData object that includes a file upload. When I submit something, I will receive the file size in bytes within the JSON response.